  "intent_precise": "Protocol Title: Using thermo_tubes (labware, slot 2), supernate_final (plate, slot 2), midi_plate_2 (deep_well_plate, slot 5), reagent_resv (reservoir, slot 5). With temperature module, magnetic module. (1) Transfer from source (multiple wells) to destination (multiple wells). (2) Engage magnets for bead separation. (3) Incubate for 5 minutes. (4) Wait 2 seconds. (5) Transfer 3\u00b5L from source to destination. (6) Engage magnets for bead separation. (7) Wait 2 seconds. (8) Transfer 10\u00b5L from source to destination. (9) Mix 10 times at 120\u00b5L. (10) Disengage magnets to release beads. (11) Incubate for 5 minutes. (12) Engage magnets for bead separation. (13) Incubate for 5 minutes. (14) Transfer 45\u00b5L from source to destination. (15) Disengage magnets to release beads. (16) Transfer 10\u00b5L from source to destination. (17) Wait 30 seconds. (18) Engage magnets for bead separation. (19) Incubate for 5 minutes. (20) Transfer 100\u00b5L from source to destination. (21) Transfer 3\u00b5L from source to destination. (22) Incubate for 5 minutes. (23) Disengage magnets to release beads. (24) Transfer 32\u00b5L from source to destination. (25) Mix 10 times at 40\u00b5L. (26) Incubate for 2 minutes. (27) Engage magnets for bead separation. (28) Incubate for 2 minutes. (29) Transfer 30\u00b5L from source to destination.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation. (volumes 3\u00b5L-125\u00b5L, ~32 min total)",
  "intent": "For this magnetic bead separation protocol, you'll be working with thermo_tubes and supernate_final plate in slot 2, plus midi_plate_2 deep well plate and reagent reservoir in slot 5, using both temperature and magnetic modules. Start by transferring samples between wells, then engage the magnets and incubate for 5 minutes before making your first small transfers of 3\u00b5L and 10\u00b5L with 2-second waits between each step. After mixing 10 times at 120\u00b5L volume and cycling through magnet engagement/disengagement with various incubation periods (5 minutes each), you'll do a series of transfers including 45\u00b5L, 10\u00b5L, 100\u00b5L, 3\u00b5L, and 32\u00b5L volumes, mixing the last one 10 times at 40\u00b5L. Finish with 2-minute incubations while magnets are engaged, then transfer your final 30\u00b5L to complete the protocol.",
